$ lxcore.sys

? `lxcore.sys` is the kernel-mode Ring 0 driver which implements all the functionality that a Linux appliction inside of a Pico process will see.
-
This driver works together with `→ Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/drivers/lxss_sys` to coordinate → Windows/Subsystem-for-Linux#wsl-syscall[Linux syscalls with the NT Kernel].

links:
  Alex Ionescu: → https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ionescu007/lxss/6a3040fadff5ce43d7bfd638a4e5d7dfe8780143/WSL-BlueHat-Final.pdf[Gaining visibility into Linux binaries on Windows: Defend and understand WSL]
